{
  "texts": [
    "The poor thermal conductivity of common dielectric materials also produces cooling issues in dry etching processes and prohibits the directional etching required for producing high-aspect ratio dielectric meta-units 161.",
    "We expect the development of novel dielectric materials and nanoscale 3D alignment methods to be crucial for realizing metasurface networks formed by successive layers of jointly-optimized meta-layers.",
    "In general, nanofabrication methods that allow scalable, low-cost production of metasurface networks are essential for the wide-scale use of such optical processors.",
    "One promising approach to realizing large-scale parallel nanofabrication is photolithography which can replicate the metasurface designs defined on a photomask on transparent wafers (Supplementary Fig.",
    "S2d) 162."
  ]
}